-  <a href="#security">Security</a>
-</nav>
-
-<!-- 安装 -->
-<h2 id="install">📥 Installation</h2>
-<h3>macOS</h3>
-<ol>
-  <li>Go to <a href="https://github.com/yueraaaa/NewReader/releases/latest" class="release-link">GitHub Releases</a> and download the latest <code>NewReader.dmg</code></li>
-  <li>Open the DMG and drag <strong>NewReader.app</strong> into <code>/Applications</code></li>
-  <li>On first launch, if you see "unable to verify developer", go to <strong>System Settings → Privacy &amp; Security</strong> and click "Open Anyway"</li>
-</ol>
-<h3>iOS</h3>
-<p>Build and install via Xcode. Open <code>Package.swift</code>, select the <strong>NewReaderiOS</strong> target, connect your iPhone, and run.</p>
-
-<!-- 添加订阅源 -->
-<h2 id="subscribe">📡 Adding Feeds</h2>
-<ol>
-  <li>Press <code>⌘N</code> or click the <strong>+</strong> button in the toolbar</li>
-  <li>Enter an RSS / Atom / JSON Feed URL</li>
-  <li>Click "Subscribe" — the feed title and articles will appear in the sidebar</li>
-</ol>
-<p>OPML import supported: sidebar <strong>⋯</strong> → Import OPML, select a <code>.opml</code> file.</p>
-
-<!-- 订阅源管理 -->
-<h2 id="manage">📁 Feed Management</h2>
-<ul>
-  <li><strong>Refresh</strong>: Right-click a feed → Refresh, or use the toolbar refresh button</li>
-  <li><strong>Rename</strong>: Right-click a feed → Rename</li>
-  <li><strong>Mark All Read</strong>: Right-click a feed → Mark all as read</li>
-  <li><strong>Delete</strong>: Right-click a feed → Delete</li>
-  <li><strong>Categories</strong>: Create categories to organize feeds; collapsible, renamable, deletable</li>
-</ul>
-
-<!-- AI -->
-<h2 id="ai">🤖 AI Summarization &amp; Translation</h2>
-<p>Supports OpenAI-compatible APIs (OpenAI, DeepSeek, Qwen, etc.).</p>
-<ol>
-  <li>Open Settings (<code>⌘,</code>) → <strong>AI</strong> tab</li>
-  <li>Select a model (DeepSeek-V3 / DeepSeek-R1)</li>
-  <li>In articles: toolbar <strong>✨</strong> to summarize, <strong>🌐</strong> to translate</li>
-</ol>
-<div class="note">AI summarization and translation are provided by the NewReader backend — no need to configure API keys yourself.</div>
-
-<!-- TTS -->
-<h2 id="tts">🔊 Text-to-Speech (TTS)</h2>
-<table>
-  <tr><th>Engine</th><th>Description</th><th>Network</th></tr>
-  <tr><td>Apple System Voice</td><td>Built-in macOS / iOS engine, supports Mandarin, English, Japanese, Korean</td><td>Offline</td></tr>
-  <tr><td>Custom TTS API</td><td>Connect any TTS provider for natural, fluid voice</td><td>Online</td></tr>
-</table>
-<p>Click the toolbar <strong>🔊</strong> button while reading — supports pause and resume. Settings → Voice tab to switch engines and configure custom endpoints and API keys.</p>
-
-<!-- 全文提取 -->
-<h2 id="fulltext">📄 Full-text Extraction</h2>
-<p>Some feeds only provide summaries. Click the toolbar <strong>📄</strong> button to auto-fetch the full article from the original link.</p>
-
-<!-- iCloud -->
-<h2 id="icloud">☁️ iCloud Cross-Device Sync</h2>
-<p>Automatically sync feeds, articles, and read status across devices with the same Apple ID.</p>
-<table>
-  <tr><th>Synced Data</th><th>Description</th></tr>
-  <tr><td>Feeds &amp; categories</td><td>List structure auto-synced</td></tr>
-  <tr><td>Read status</td><td>Read / unread synced</td></tr>
-  <tr><td>Preferences</td><td>Theme, language, etc. synced</td></tr>
-  <tr><td>API Keys</td><td>Not synced for security</td></tr>
-</table>
-
-<!-- 离线缓存 -->
-<h2 id="cache">💾 Offline Cache</h2>
-<p>Articles are automatically cached locally — read even without internet. Settings → Storage to view cache size and clear with one click.</p>
-
-<!-- 快捷键 -->
-<h2 id="shortcuts">⌨️ Keyboard Shortcuts</h2>
-<div class="shortcut-grid">
-  <div class="shortcut-card"><kbd>⌘N</kbd><span>Add Feed</span></div>
-  <div class="shortcut-card"><kbd>⌘,</kbd><span>Settings</span></div>
-  <div class="shortcut-card"><kbd>⌘R</kbd><span>Refresh Feeds</span></div>
-  <div class="shortcut-card"><kbd>⌘F</kbd><span>Search Articles</span></div>
-  <div class="shortcut-card"><kbd>J</kbd><span>Next Article</span></div>
-  <div class="shortcut-card"><kbd>K</kbd><span>Previous Article</span></div>
-  <div class="shortcut-card"><kbd>Space</kbd><span>Scroll Down</span></div>
-  <div class="shortcut-card"><kbd>⌘W</kbd><span>Reading Workspace</span></div>
-</div>
-
-<!-- 安全 -->
-<h2 id="security">🔐 Security Design</h2>
-<ul>
-  <li>API keys encrypted in system Keychain — never stored in plaintext</li>
-  <li>WKWebView with JavaScript disabled + CSP policy to block script injection</li>
-  <li>URLs restricted to http/https only, private IP / localhost blocked (SSRF prevention)</li>
-  <li>HTML sanitization: strips script, iframe, and event handlers</li>
-  <li>OPML import capped at 5 MB</li>
-  <li>macOS App Sandbox with process-level isolation</li>
-</ul>
-
-</div>
-
